        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Sessions page: use numeric input for Limit field",
        "body": "Summary\r\n\r\nFixes the Sessions page Limit field so it uses a numeric input instead of accepting arbitrary text.\r\n\r\nProblem\r\n\r\nThe field was implemented as a plain text input and passed raw string values into filter state. This allowed invalid values such as abc or eyertyl to be entered without validation.\r\n\r\nChanges\r\nchanged Limit input to type=\"number\"\r\nadded numeric constraints with min=\"1\" and step=\"1\"\r\nparsed input before passing it into onFiltersChange\r\nfall back to undefined for invalid or empty values\r\nSteps to Reproduce\r\nOpen Control -> Sessions\r\nEnter a non-numeric value into the Limit field\r\nObserve that the old implementation accepts invalid text without validation\r\nExpected Behavior\r\n\r\nLimit should accept only valid numeric input.\r\n\r\nActual Behavior\r\n\r\nThe field accepts arbitrary text and forwards it as filter state.\r\n\r\nResult\r\n\r\nThe field now behaves like a numeric limit input and prevents inval\r\n<img width=\"1648\" height=\"879\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-04-20 172313\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/00bb92b0-ea58-448b-8c03-37a5fd5c579f\" />\r\nid text-based values from being used.\r\n\r\n",
